{"title":"*Kaput: The End of the German Miracle*","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/907923011/0/marginalrevolution~Kaput-The-End-of-the-German-Miracle.html","date":1731656873000,"content":"<p>By Wolfgang Münchau,<a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/KAPUT-Wolfgang-M%C3%BCnchau/dp/1800753438/ref=sr_1_1?crid=350AQY1SNWRTZ&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.4e0O-fskI0wFRfn_A1s5Ng.D8twaZ6dSkqAOH5XDyrOS4Aoq6v9-yUARslk0Gm4dEw&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Kaput%3A+The+End+of+the+German+Miracle&amp;qid=1731621033&amp;sprefix=kaput+the+end+of+the+german+miracle%2Caps%2C77&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\"> this book</a> is the best and most detailed account of the German economic decline to date.  Excerpt:</p>\r\n<blockquote><p>In 2018, the federal government promised that Germany would become a world leader in artificial intelligence.</p></blockquote>\r\n<p>As if they don’t understand that such efforts are more than just a play toy.  The overall lesson I took away from this book (my interpretation, not the author’s) is that if a country does not have enough ambition and seriousness in its businesses and education systems, sooner or later it will not have that in its government either.</p>\r\n<p>Another lesson is that the world, overall, is working less well than you might think.</p>\r\n<p>I am sad to recommend this one.  My primary reservation is that the author does not do enough to diagnose Germany’s obvious cultural malaise as an underlying root cause.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/11/kaput-the-end-of-the-german-miracle.html\">*Kaput: The End of the German Miracle*</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/907923011/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><